g.text: $ rice-factor --help
Usage: rice-factor [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGS]...
LLM-Assisted Development System - Artifacts as IR, LLMs as Compilers
| --version -v Show version and exit. |
| --verbose -V Enable verbose output. |
| --quiet -q Suppress non-essential output. |
| --install-completion Install completion for the current shell. |
| --show-completion Show completion for the current shell, to |
| copy it or customize the installation. |
| --help Show this message and exit. |
| scaffold Create file structure from ScaffoldPlan. |
| impl Generate implementation diff for a specific file. |
| review Review and approve/reject pending diffs. |
| apply Apply approved diffs to the codebase. |
| test Run tests against the locked TestPlan. |
| diagnose Analyze test/validation failures and suggest fixes. |
| approve Approve an artifact, transitioning it from DRAFT to APPROVED |
| status. |
| lock Lock an artifact, making it permanently immutable. |
| validate Run validations on project artifacts and code. |
| resume Resume after a failure or interruption. |
| reconcile Generate reconciliation plan for detected drift. |
| capabilities Show available refactoring tools and their capabilities. |
| models Show registered LLM models and their capabilities. |
| viz Generate dependency graphs from artifacts. |
| docs Generate documentation from artifacts. |
| tui Launch interactive TUI mode. |
| init Initialize a new rice-factor project |
| plan Generate planning artifacts |
| refactor Refactor commands for structural code changes. |
| override Override and reconciliation commands. |
| ci CI/CD validation commands. |
| audit Audit commands for drift detection and health checks. |
| artifact Artifact lifecycle management commands. |
| migrate Artifact schema migration commands. |
| metrics Metrics commands for viewing and exporting metrics. |
| batch Batch artifact operations |
| usage LLM usage tracking commands. |
| agents CLI coding agent management commands. |
| web Web interface commands for rice-factor. |
